TY  - JOUR
T1  - On Sequencing n Jobs on One Machine to Minimize the Number of Late Jobs
AU  - Maxwell, William L.
Y1  - 1970/01/01
PY  - 1970
DA  - 1970/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.16.5.295
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.16.5.295
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 295
EP  - 297
VL  - 16
IS  - 5
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - An integer programming formulation for the problem of sequencing jobs on a single machine to minimize the number of late jobs is developed. The structure of the formulation is exploited to obtain the easily stated algorithm (previously developed by Moore [5]) for the solution of the problem and then to compare it to other similar allocation problems, among which is the Knapsack problem.
AB  - An integer programming formulation for the problem of sequencing jobs on a single machine to minimize the number of late jobs is developed. The structure of the formulation is exploited to obtain the easily stated algorithm (previously developed by Moore [5]) for the solution of the problem and then to compare it to other similar allocation problems, among which is the Knapsack problem.
