TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Method for Solving the Indefinite Quadratic Programming Problem
AU  - Mueller, Raymond K.
Y1  - 1970/01/01
PY  - 1970
DA  - 1970/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.16.5.333
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.16.5.333
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 333
EP  - 339
VL  - 16
IS  - 5
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A method is developed for obtaining a solution to the quadratic programming problem with an indefinite quadratic objective function. A search procedure using gradient projection is the core of the method. However at each step an alternate direction to gradient projection is proposed and two methods are given to continue after the revised gradient projection procedure terminates. Although convergence to the solution is not guaranteed, good results were obtained for fifty-seven problems used to test the method.
AB  - A method is developed for obtaining a solution to the quadratic programming problem with an indefinite quadratic objective function. A search procedure using gradient projection is the core of the method. However at each step an alternate direction to gradient projection is proposed and two methods are given to continue after the revised gradient projection procedure terminates. Although convergence to the solution is not guaranteed, good results were obtained for fifty-seven problems used to test the method.
SN  - 0025-1909
